column12: Truck bed access system and method of use
column13: A truck system includes a truck bed having a first side, a second side, and a back end; a first panel slidingly engaged with the first side; and one or more rails to facilitate the sliding engagement of the first panel with the first side; the first side is positioned above a first wheel; and sliding the first panel from a first position to a second position provides access to an interior of the bed.

column12: GETRIEBEABTRIEBSWELLEN-SCHWINGUNGSDÄMPFER
column13: Ein Getriebe umfasst ein Getriebegehäuse mit einem Abtriebswellenflansch mit einem zentralen Durchgang. Eine Abtriebswelle erstreckt sich durch den zentralen Durchgang. Die Abtriebswelle definiert eine Wellenachse und schließt einen axialen Endabschnitt ein. Ein Schwingungsdämpfer ist an dem axialen Endabschnitt der Abtriebswelle angebracht und ein mechanisches Befestigungselement wird von dem axialen Endabschnitt der Abtriebswelle aufgenommen. Das mechanische Befestigungselement verbindet den Schwingungsdämpfer wirkend mit der Abtriebswelle.

column12: Transmission output shaft vibration dampener
column13: A transmission includes a transmission housing having an output shaft flange including a central passage. An output shaft extends through the central passage. The output shaft defines a shaft axis andincluding an axial end portion. A vibration dampener is mounted to the axial end portion of the output shaft, and a mechanical fastener is received by the axial end portion of the output shaft. The mechanical fastener operatively connects the vibration dampener to the output shaft.

column12: Clamping device
column13: The present disclosure relates to a clamp (10) having a first body portion (11) and a second body portion (12) that define corresponding mutually opposed first and second engagement configurations (14, 18). The first body portion (11) and the second body portion (12) are movable relative to each other to displace the first engagement formation (14) and the second engagement formation (18) toward and away from each other. An actuator (13) is provided for displacing the first engagement configuration (14) and the second engagement configuration (18) towards each other. The actuator (13) comprises: a cam (21) movably coupled to one of the first body portion (11) and the second body portion (12); and a cam follower (22) coupled to the other of the first body portion (11) and the second body portion (12). The cam (21) has a cam surface (23-1, 23-2) for cooperating with the cam follower (22).
column15: LEMON GUY R;;DUPRE DANIEL W;;GOEK JAMES H;;SCHWAB JAMES R;;ROMEO MICHAEL K

column12: PROCESS FOR PRODUCING FLUIDS OF ENHANCED THERMAL STABILITY
column13: The present invention provides for synthetic ester lubricants having enhanced thermal stability prepared by oxidatively treating a substrate comprising an ester lubricant at elevated temperatures in excess of 200 °C for a period of time sufficient to substantially oxidize impurities present in the lubricant, but insufficient to substantially oxidize the ester or to substantially decompose it. The process results in a predecomposition of the most reactive species of the substrate to the more stable species. The resulting ester lubricants so treated are found to exhibit enhanced thermal stability at temperatures of 375 °C and above thereby rendering them more effective as lubricants in high temperature applications and more stable over longer periods of time.

column12: OPTICALLY TRANSMISSIVE SUBSTRATE HAVING A FIDUCIAL MARK AND METHODS OF ALIGNING OPTICALLY TRANSMISSIVE SUBSTRATES
column13: An article comprises an optically transmissive substrate comprising a plurality of functional elements and an integral fiducial mark. The substrate has a critical angle for total internal reflection, and a length and a width defining a reference plane. The substrate comprises an integral fiducial mark disposed on the major surface. The integral fiducial mark comprises at least one substantially ellipse-like feature formed by first and second frustoconical surfaces that together with a reference line that is normal to the reference plane define respective first and second half angles. The first and second half angles are less than or equal to 90 degrees minus the critical angle for total internal reflection expressed in degrees. A method comprises: providing an optically transmissive substrate according to the present disclosure; precisely detecting a position of the fiducial mark with aid of a machine vision system; and optionally precisely aligning the substrate.

column12: METHOD AND INTEGRATED PROCESS FOR THE CARBOXYLATION OF FURAN DERIVED CARBOXYLIC ACIDS TO 2,5-FURANDICARBOXYLIC ACID
column13: A process for carboxylation of a furoate slurry to produce FDCA, especially 2,5-FDCA, includes the steps of: feeding a slurry containing a suspension fluid, furoate, a surfactant and an alkali metal carbonate to a carboxylation reactor; and feeding a flow of CO 2 to the carboxylation reactor at flow conditions sufficient to suspend the slurry in the reactor and react the furoate with CO2 to form 2,5-FDCA. A fully integrated process is also disclosed.

column12: centralizador de poço e método para instalar um centralizador em um poço
column13: centralizador de poço, método para instalar um centralizador em um poço e método de fabricação de um centralizador de poço. a presente invenção refere-se geralmente aos centra lizadores do tipo arco usados durante operações em poços de petróleo e/ou gás. mais particularmente, a presente invenção refere-se aos centralizadores do tipo arco usados em colunas de revestimento ou outros tubos e acessórios inseridos nos ditos poços. o centralizador (1) de poço compreende um elemento tubular (10) que tem um furo atravessante central (11), uma superfície externa (18), e os primeiro (12) e segundo (15) canais circunferências dispostos na dita superfície externa (18); um primeiro elemento de banda (101) disposto de maneira giratória no dito primeiro canal circunferencial (12); um segundo elemento de banda (103) disposto de maneira giratória no dito segundo canal circunferencial (15); e uma pluralidade de elementos de mola em arco (110), sendo que cada um tem uma primeira extremidade (111) e uma segunda extremidade (111), em que a dita primeira extremidade (111) é conectada a o dito primeiro elemento de banda (101) e a dita segunda extremidade (111) é conectada ao dito segundo elemento de banda (103).

column12: Well centralizer
column13: A centralizer assembly having a tubular body member with upper and lower channels extending around the external surface of said central tubular body member. A bow spring assembly having bow spring members is installed around the outer surface of the tubular body member and can rotate about the outer surface of the central tubular body member. Bow spring heel supports prevent the bow spring members from contacting the outer surface of the central tubular member when compressed. Non-abrasive materials prevent damage to wellhead or other polished bore receptacles. A robust bolster frame protects the centralizer assembly during shipping, storage or other periods of non-use.

column12: Stator bar handler and method
column13: A flexible bar handler comprises a mobile carriage; a lift boom comprising a longitudinal shaft rotatably attached to rotate around a vertical axis of the carriage to swing an end of the shaft back and forth and pivotally attached to pivot around a horizontal axis of the carriage to raise and lower the end of the shaft; and a lift bracket comprising an elongated rail with receptor-shaped cross section to lengthwise accommodate a bar, the lift bracket being attached at a point on its length at a terminal end of the longitudinal shaft opposed to a counter weight attached at an opposite terminal end of the shaft, wherein the lift bracket is pivotally attached to a horizontal pin at the point to permit the lift bracket to tilt to one side or the other so as to raise and lower the lift bracket ends. A method of handling a stator bar; comprises loading the bar into a lift bracket comprising an elongated rail with receptor-shaped cross section, wherein the lift bracket is part of a flexible bar handler; transporting the bar to an unloading area in proximity to a stator slot of a stator core; manipulating the lift bracket by (i) swinging an end of the shaft back and forth, (ii) raising or lowering an end of the shaft, (iii) tilting the lift bracket to tilt the bracket to one side or the other so as to raise and lower the lift bracket ends or (iv) moving the bar forward or backward to position the bar for unloading into the stator slot; and unloading the bar into the slot.

column12: Stator bar handler and method
column13: A flexible bar handler that comprises a mobile carriage; a lift boom assembly rotatably attached to rotate around a vertical axis of the carriage to swing a distal end of the boom assembly back and forth and pivotally attached to pivot around a horizontal axis of the carriage to raise and lower the distal end of the boom assembly; and a lift bracket comprising an elongated rail with receptor-shaped cross section to lengthwise accommodate a bar, the lift bracket being attached at a point on its length at the distal end of the longitudinal boom assembly opposed to a counter weight attached at an opposite proximal end of the boom assembly, wherein the lift bracket is pivotally attached to a horizontal pin at the point to permit the lift bracket to tilt to one side or the other so as to raise and lower the lift bracket ends. A method of handling a stator bar; comprises loading the bar into a lift bracket comprising an elongated rail with receptor-shaped cross section, wherein the lift bracket is part of a flexible bar handler that includes a mobile carriage; manipulating the lift bracket by (i) swinging an end of the boom assembly back and forth, (ii) raising or lowering an end of the boom assembly, (iii) tilting the lift bracket to tilt the bracket to one side or the other so as to raise and lower the lift bracket ends or (iv) moving the bar forward or backward by the mobile carriage to position the bar for unloading into the stator slot; and unloading the bar into the slot.

column12: AGLOMERANTES BASADOS EN RESINAS DE FENOL-FORMALDEHIDO Y MELAMINA-FORMALDEHIDO .
column13: Un aglomerante que comprende una resina melamina-formaldehídoo genol-formaldehído con 1 a 95% peso basado en sólidos de resina de un prepolímero de urea cíclica ya sea durante la fabricación de la resina o agregado posteriormente a la resina en la que el prepolímero de urea cíclica tiene una relación de mol de urea: formaldehído: amoníaco o un amino primario de 0.1 a 1.0:0.1 a 3.0:0.1 a 1.0. El aglomerante de la reivindicación 1 en el que el prepolímero de urea cíclica se prepara mezclando urea, formaldehído y amoníaco o un amino primario y calentando la mezcla a un pH alcalino de 60 a 105°C durante un tiempo suficiente para completar la reacción.

column12: DEVICE AND METHOD FOR HANDLING STATOR BAR
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a handling device for conveying and positioning a stator bar.

SOLUTION: The handling device 10 of a flexible bar is rotatably attached to a self-travelling carrier 14 so as to rotate around a perpendicular axis of the self-travelling carrier 14 and turn a distal end of the self-travelling carrier back and forth. The device includes a lift boom assembly 12 pivotally attached so as to pivot around a horizontal axis of the carrier 14 and raise and lower the distal end, an elongated rail 114 having a receptor shape in cross section for housing the bar in the longitudinal direction, and a lift bracket 16 facing to a counter weight attached on a near end facing to the boom assembly 12 and attached in a point position on an entire length on a distal end of the boom assembly 12 in the vertical direction. The lift bracket 16 is pivotally attached on a horizontal pin 106 in the point position and the lift bracket can incline on one side or another side.

column12: CYCLIC UREA-FORMALDEHYDE PREPOLYMER FOR USE IN PHENOL-FORMALDEHYDE AND MELAMINE-FORMALDEHYDE RESIN-BASED BINDERS
column13: The preparation of phenol-formaldehyde and melamine-formaldehyde resin-based binders extended with a cyclic urea-formaldehyde prepolymer and to products prepared using the binders. More particularly, the invention relates to cyclic urea prepolymer comprising urea, formaldehyde, and ammonia or a primary amine which, when added to a phenol-formaldehyde or melamine-formaldehyde based resin, results in a useful binder for the manufacturer numerous articles.

column12: "prepolìmero de uréia cìclica-aldeìdo fórmico para emprego em aglutinantes à base de resina de fenol-aldeìdo fórmico e de melamina-aldeìdo fórmico"
column13: "PREPOLìMERO DE URéIA CìCLICA-ALDEìDO FóRMICO PARA EMPREGO EM AGLUTINANTES à BASE DE RESINA DE FENOL-ALDEìDO FóRMICO E DE MELAMINA-ALDEìDO FóRMICO" Trata-se de uma preparação de aglutinantes à base de resinas de fenol-aldeído fórmico e melamina-aldeido fórmico diluídos com um prepolímero de uréia cíclica-aldeído fórmico e produtos preparados usando os aglutinantes. Mais especificamente a invenção se refere a prepolímero de uréia cíclica compreendendo uréia, aldeído fórmico e amónia ou uma amina primária que, quando acrescentada a uma resina à base de fenol-aldeído fórmico ou melamina-aldeído fórmico, resulta em um aglutinante útil para a fabricação de diversos artigos.

column12: Method of semi-automatic data collection, data analysis, and model generation for the performance analysis of enterprise applications
column13: A method of semi-automatic data collection, data analysis and model generation for performance analysis of computer networks and software is provided. The invention provides a graphical user interface which indicates the overall data flow in the performance analysis process and guides the user through the proper sequence of steps in that process. Underneath the graphical user interface, the invention provides software tools which include novel data pipeline for transformation of network traces, resource data and application data into organized hash tables, and further into spreadsheets for introduction into computer network simulation programs. The invention also provides novel algorithms for recognizing transaction and parentage between transactions from low level network trace data. The invention further provides novel methods of visualization of trace data and transaction and parentage associations.
